# ====================================================================
# hex2 (minimal) for riscv64 UEFI -- multi-char labels + RISC-V relocs
# ====================================================================
#
# Beyond hex1: multi-character label names, several relocation
# types matching RISC-V instruction encodings, and the
# `%label>base` "trampoline" syntax used by linker scripts.
#
# Token catalog:
#   :name      label define (no bytes emitted)
#   %name      relative 4-byte (target - IP)        I-type displacement context
#   &name      absolute 4-byte (target)
#   ~name      U-type encoding XOR (auipc/lui hi20)
#   !name      I-type encoding XOR (addi/jalr lo12 with sign rounding)
#   @name      B-type encoding XOR (branch displacement)
#   $name      J-type encoding XOR (jal displacement)
#   .name      raw byte from named label table
#   %name>base relative offset against an explicit base label
#               (instead of current IP). Used to anchor PE32+
#               header fields to the section start.
#   #/;        comment to end-of-line
#
# Two-pass design (same shape as hex1):
#   Pass 1: scan input, build a linked list of label entries
#           (NAME, TARGET, NEXT). Hex bytes advance IP, tokens
#           advance IP by their final emitted size.
#   Pass 2: re-read input from buf_start, emit hex bytes, encode
#           and emit each token by walking the label list to find
#           NAME and computing displacement vs IP (or vs base).
#
# Memory layout:
#   - 16 MiB pool allocated up front; first 2 KiB reserved as
#     scratch buffer (for token name comparison), remainder is the
#     "heap" used to lay down label-entry structs and the
#     in-memory output buffer.
#   - Label entry struct: NAME (8B ptr), NEXT (8B ptr), TARGET (8B IP)
#                         + variable-length name bytes after the
#                         struct, NUL-terminated, padded to 8.
#   - HEAD (s11) points at the most recently inserted entry.
#
# Encoding helpers (the four ~/!/@/$ paths) build the
# instruction-shaped XOR mask in t3 then s1 ^= t3 over the existing
# (placeholder) bytes. The placeholder bytes were emitted with
# everything-but-the-displacement already set; XORing the
# displacement bits in flips them to the correct value without a
# read-modify-write cycle on memory.
#
# Generated by gen-hex2-rv64.py.
# Total size: 3328 bytes, Code size: 2700 bytes.
#
# Calling convention:
#   s0 = heap pointer (label entries + output buffer)
#   s1 = ImageHandle initially, repurposed for byte-shift accumulator
#        in mid-flow then restored from image_handle_data
#   s2 = boot_services
#   s3 = rootdir, s4 = fin -> later out_pos, s5 = fout
#   s6 = root_device, s7 = nibble toggle (-1/0)
#   s8 = nibble accumulator
#   s9 = scratch_base (set during init from allocated pool)
#   s10 = IP counter, s11 = HEAD of label list

4D 5A                                            # MZ signature
00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 # DOS header padding
80 00 00 00                                      # PE header offset = 0x80
