93 02 10 00
93 92 B2 00                                      # t0=0x800
33 84 5C 00                                      # s0=heap (scratch+2K)
# === GetFileInfo to discover real file size ========================
# We need the *exact* file size (not just the read return count)
# because cc_riscv64 hex2 outputs sometimes contain trailing zero
# pads from the FAT cluster boundary; without a real size we'd
# scan past EOF into garbage. EFI_FILE_INFO is variable-length;
# 256 bytes is enough for any reasonable filename.
13 01 01 EF                                      # alloc GetInfo buffer
93 02 00 10
23 30 51 00                                      # buf_size = 256
13 05 0A 00                                      # fin
97 15 00 00                                      # auipc a1, %hi(FILE_INFO_GUID)
